Series 2 [2005] (176mins)
New characters for Series 2 included camp Derek Faye.
The show also got its first Christmas special at the
end of this year.

Episode 1
Lauren is not impressed by her teacher's
dress sense, Nan's television breaks down
and Derek Faye is insulted by a doctor.

Episode 2
The Aga Saga Woman is terrified by a Geordie
babysitter, Irene & Vern describe their
encounter with Desmond Tutu and Nan's visit
at the doctor soon turns unpleasant.

Episode 3
Ivan & Trudy present their 'wig emporium',
Derek Faye purchases a David Beckham calendar
and are hospital nurses stealing Nan's personal
belongings?

Episode 4
Nan is introduced to Jamie's girlfriend who is
a little sensitive about her nose, a drunk bride
reveals too much truth, Lauren gets a tattoo of
her boyfriend and Irene is excited about meeting
Mikhail Gorbachov in her burger van.

Episode 5
Paul meets Sam's parents who are still laughing
about their fancy dress party, Bernie meets a new
member of staff and Nan comes home from a funeral
and discovers that Lena owed her money.

Episode 6
Janice & Ray discuss their gourmet's experience,
Kate & Ellen are talking about the most offensive
word in the office, Lauren questions her teacher's
sexuality and Nan receives a visit from an old friend.

Series 3 [2006] (167mins)
By the time this series started, The Catherine Tate Show
was one of the biggest comedies in the country and thus
nearly 5 million viewers tuned in to see if Lauren was
still not 'bovvered'.

Episode 1
A Northern Irish mum is delighted that her son
is gay. Meanwhile, Nan visits an old friend in
hospital and Lauren takes a job in a burger bar.

Episode 2
Lauren joins the cheerleaders to impress Ryan, 50s
landlady Ma Willow makes her first appearance and
Nan has a mouse in her house.

Episode 3
Derek Faye meets Bonnie Langford, Lauren receives
a proposal, Nan has a new neighbour from upstairs
and Bernie's brothers and sisters from Ireland
come for a visit.

Episode 4
Gingers For Justice take to the rooftops, Lauren
causes trouble in science class and The Aga Saga
Woman and her children are terrified when a
mechanic brings over a courtesy car whilst her
Land Rover is being repaired.

Episode 5
Nan appears on Paul O'Grady's teatime show and
broadcasts her horrible views to the nation.
The Aga Saga Woman takes a wrong turn into
Tottenham and Lauren refuses to speak French
for a French oral exam.

Episode 6
Lauren almost gets married, Derek gets a massage,
Georgie does another fund raiser - this time for
dwarves, Janice & Ray talk about a sandwich with
no bread, Nan's sister comes over from Spain and
Essex couple Paul & Sam return with more laughs.
